<!-- 
## TextArea

### Description
A customizable text area component for user input, which is styled and can be configured with various properties like placeholder text and requirement status.

### How to use
1. Import the `TextArea` component into your Astro file.

2. Use the component with the desired props:

<TextArea 
  legendText="Enter Details" 
  placeholderText="Type your message here..." 
  required={true} 
  fieldId="message" 
  fieldName="userMessage" 
/>



### Props List
- **legendText**: *string* (optional) - The text for the legend of the text area.
- **placeholderText**: *string* (optional) - The placeholder text displayed inside the text area.
- **required**: *boolean* (optional) - Indicates whether the text area is required.
- **fieldId**: *string* (optional) - The id attribute for the text area.
- **fieldName**: *string* (optional) - The name attribute for the text area.
-->
---
//css stylesheet
import "../../styles/global.css"

//props
const {legendText, placeholderText, required, fieldId, fieldName} = Astro.props
---

<fieldset class="fieldset">
    <legend class="fieldset-legend">{legendText}</legend>
    <textarea id={fieldId} name={fieldName} class="textarea" placeholder={placeholderText} required={required}></textarea>
  </fieldset>